Subject: [PATCH 2/5] fix(consolidate): address critic-blocking cancel +
 history regressions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Pre-merge critic review found 2 critical + 2 significant regressions
in the headless+TUI cutover. All four fixed before opening PR.

## C1 — Adapter never raised AbortError → headless exited 0 on ESC

Cancellation regressed: ESC mid-run flipped abort_controller, query()
set a terminal-state to aborted_streaming/aborted_tools, the
adapter returned normally. Headless saw empty response_text +
exit_code=0 (legacy raised AbortError → exit 130 + 'cancelled' event);
TUI posted blank AgentRunFinished with no error string.

Fix: after the async for msg in query(...) completes, inspect
holder.value. If terminal reason in {aborted_streaming,
aborted_tools, interrupted}, raise AbortError so the callers'
existing except AbortError paths fire unchanged.

## C2 — User's cancel signal didn't reach provider.chat_stream_response

The adapter minted a fresh AbortController instead of accepting the
caller's. The provider's chat_stream_response listens on
QueryParams.abort_controller.signal to tear down HTTP mid-stream;
since that was the fresh controller (not the user's), ESC during a
tool-use-only turn (no message yields → no per-event bridge fires)
waited the full model latency before bailing.

Fix: adapter accepts abort_controller directly (already in
signature). Headless + TUI now pass their owning controller instead
of just .signal. Legacy cancel_signal=signal path preserved with
its bridge for back-compat.

## S1 — API errors and meta messages persisted into user Conversation

The on_message callback in headless+TUI persists every yielded
AssistantMessage / UserMessage. Legacy run_agent_loop never added
isApiErrorMessage / isMeta messages to the user's conversation; the
new path did. Multi-prompt sessions saw 'I had trouble earlier...'
hallucinations from the model + PTL death spirals from
prompt_too_long error text persisted as assistant output.

Fix: adapter skips on_message dispatch for messages where
isApiErrorMessage or isMeta is True. Also doesn't count those toward
num_turns or use them as response_text.

## S2 — Conversation.max_history=100 silently truncated long sessions

New path persists tool_use AND tool_result blocks as separate
messages (legacy persisted only assistant text + tool_result via
add_tool_result_message). A 30-turn agentic run is ~120 messages —
past the cap — and pop(0) removes the ORIGINAL user prompt,
degrading subsequent turns.

Fix: bump max_history from 100 to 2000. Compaction
(CompressionPipeline / /compact) is the right tool for serious
context management; this cap is just a memory-safety backstop and
2000 covers a long agentic session without changing semantics.

## S3 — Bare except in _persist swallowed corruption errors

Both headless and TUI wrapped session.conversation.add_message in
except Exception: pass. If the conversation got corrupted
(malformed blocks, etc), the next API call would 400 with
'tool_use IDs must match tool_result IDs' and the proximate cause
would be invisible.

Fix: log via logger.exception in TUI (UI keeps running); re-raise in
headless (single-shot, fail loud is right).

## Test plan

- [x] tests/test_agent_loop_compat.py — 6 passed (1 test updated to
  expect AbortError from cancel-signal case per C1)
- [x] tests/test_headless_cli.py — 10 passed
- [x] tests/test_advisor_* — 75 passed (no regression)
- [x] tests/test_app_state.py — 16 passed
- [x] tests/tui/ — 525 passed (no regression)
- Live: re-ran haiku-4-5 + opus-4-7 advisor via litellm in headless;
  exit 0, file created, advisor invocable end-to-end.

